<br>
I agree with toast on this one.  Skalds need something to increase our offensive abilities.  As it stands most hybrids except a bard can defeat a skald 1v1.  A stave/enchance friar can completely mop the floor with a solo unbuffed skald.  They hit for far more damage than the skald, routiney I've been hit for 400s by stave/ench friars with some 600 crits.  Their self buffs make them extremely difficult to deal with, self haste, str, con, dex, af, absorb, style end reduction, end chant, dex/qui buffs make them killing machines vs most things in any straight up fight.  Through into that evade 5 and a 2h damage type for albion that doesn't require duel specing to decrease damage variance/increase damage cap and your looking at a world of hurt.  Oh lets not forget they get ip.<br>
<br>
On the subjects of wardens, which I have some experience with actually playing one, a solo warden is simply a gawd vs anyother class (including friars).  My warden is 39 blade, 49 nurture rest regrowth and has ip.  In duels and solo fights he has been able to kill any other melee class.  All it requires if halfway decent chant twisting and I can win 99% of the time since the pbt chant is instant cast so you can twist damage add then self end regen then pbt.  You have group resist buffs so assassins posions, skald/minstrel/thane spells do laughable damage.   I love my warden, its the one real character that I can solo with and win most of the time.<br>
<br>
So to sum up...<br>
Friars:<br>
-Healing class with 1.5x spec points that can spec a weapon type.<br>
-Stave seems to be 140% damage type like polearms but w/o having to duel spec.<br>
-Self end, haste, absorb, af, targeted dex/qui, str, con, dex, af increase weaponskill, speed, average damage, defense.<br>
-Evade 5 combined with even low level doddger and self dex/qui, dex can easily get friars to the evade cap. (evade&gt;parry for solo or large scale rvr)<br>
-Access to the ip realm ability.<br>
<br>
Wardens:<br>
-Healing class with 1.5x spec points that can spec a weapon type.<br>
-Self and targeted buffs increase weaponskill, speed, hitpoints, defense.<br>
-Instant cast pbt chant on a scale wearing class makes for extremely good solo win ratio while twisting da+self end+pbt.<br>
-Access to the ip realm ability.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying these classes don't have problems but they have some good group functionality, friars make great tank bait in groups since they look like caster but hit like a ton of bricks.  Also albion has access to the BoF realm ability giving friars even more survivability.<br>
<br>
Wardens arn't very effective in group combat except that they offer group resists and pbt which against melee heavy groups that use cc really gives an advantage.  They also offer TwF which is another boon to their class, since anyone in the range is interupted by it and takes a small amount of damage.<br>
<br>
This is where skalds become lacking, our hybrid melee damage and lack of enough defense hurts us.  We can either spec the majority of our points in a weapon type with little or no defensive ability or sacrifice some of our potential weaponskill to spec parry some (which is still horrible broken in large scale rvr).  As it stands the only thing a skald offers a group is speed with and moderately powerful tanking ability.  <br>
<br>
We have no battle deciding realm abilities like BoF, SoS, Baod, TwF.<br>
<br>
We don't even have a moderatly useful ability like FH or GP.<br>
<br>
We don't have enough defense compared to other hybrids.<br>
<br>
Minstrels get aa chant, sos, ip, dragonfang, evade 2.<br>
<br>
Bards get group end, pow, speed songs, evade 2, instant ae mez, moderate heals and a rez.<br>
<br>
Thanes get castable dd and ae dd spells, self str/con buffs, long range instant dd, shield spec, 2x spec points.<br>
<br>
Champs get str/con buff, str/con dex/qui debuffs, instant dd, shield spec, lw spec 2x spec points.<br>
<br>
Pallys get group end, tri resist buffs, FH, shield spec, 2x spec points.<br>
<br>
I already went over friars and wardens so no need to go over them again but as you can see compared to other hybrids we are subpar.  <br>
<br>
We only get evade 1 where minstrels and bards get evade 2 (although admitedly this is more useful for mintrels than for bards).   Mythic needs to decide whether we are a group based hybrid or a tank based hybrid.<br>
<br>
As it currently stands our only function in a keep siege is an as an rp cow for assassins or more meat for the grinder in lordroom standoffs.  In all honesty all I do in keep siege is go afk playing heal chant in the ck while I play my cave shaman who can actually do something to alter the outcome of the siege.<br>
<br>
In open field rvr we act as subpar caster/healer defenders since our mez lasts a whole 6 seconds on some tanks even if its not purged and subpar caster/healer attackers since although we can frontload damage on a single target with our dds everybody and their brother, mother, sister and nephew has body resist and group resist buffs out the wazoo.  Add in pbt, bof, sos, twf to the opposing groups arsenal and you might as well just bend over and kiss your ass goodbye unless you outnumber them 3:1.<br>
<br>
Overall the skald has some utility but not enough.  Our unique ra isn't worth the space it takes up on the heralds realm abilities page.  Our defense is laughable.  Our damage is subpar to most other hybrids (bards excluded).  Our spells are all on a resist type which anyone with half a brain has maxed, not to mention that do to the resist code they get resisted quite often.<br>
<br>
